description: Delicious snack or light lunch. My fussy 4 year old ate 3 pieces today, I was amazed.
name: Simple Zucchini Slice Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 170Â°C. Grease baking tray and line with baking paper. I used 33x23cm tray so quite flat but can use a smaller tray which would make the slice deeper (but beware would take a bit more time in the oven)
Grate carrot. Grate zucchini. (I squeeze out excess water from both). Grate cheese. Chop onion. Chop bacon. Melt butter in microwave. Whisk 6 eggs with a fork in a bowl. Sift flour.
Place flour and melted butter in to egg bowl and whisk well. Put all other ingredients in to a bowl. Combine the two bowls in one and mix well (add salt and pepper if you'd like).
Place in the greased and lined tin and put in the oven for around 40 minutes or until slightly brown on top.
